    {
      "title": "Use the first point",
      "content": "Substitute $(0,10)$ into $h(x)=a^x+b$:<br/>$$a^0+b=10$$<br/>$$1+b=10$$<br/>$$b=9$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Use the second point",
      "content": "Substitute $(-2,\\frac{226}{25})$ and use $b=9$:<br/>$$a^{-2}+9=\\frac{226}{25}$$<br/>$$a^{-2}=\\frac{1}{25}$$<br/>$$a^2=25$$<br/>Since $a$ is positive, $a=5$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Multiply the constants",
      "content": "Now multiply the two constants:<br/>$$ab=5\\cdot9=45$$<br/>The answer is <strong>C</strong>."
    }
  ]
